              "displayName": "Karthik Kambatla",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "IIRR, FairScheduler preemption is based on instantaneous fairshare. The steady fairshare is used only for WebUI purposes. \n\nIn your case, I would think minshare preemption kicks in because you specify min resources for all queues. Isn't it expected that all queues are getting the same resources the sum of which is cluster resources? Do you expect allocations different from minshare? ",
